 \lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{n^4}{n^2 + n!} = 0? 
n! \ge n(n-1)(n-2)(n-3)(n-4) \ge (n-4)^5
n >4
0 \le{n^4 \over n^2+n!} \le {n^4 \over n!} \le {n^4 \over (n-4)^5} = {{1 \over n} \over (1-{4 \over n})^5 }
n>8
(1-{4 \over n}) \ge {1 \over 2}
{n^4 \over n^2+n!} \le 2^5 {1 \over n}
n > \max(8, {2^5 \over \epsilon})
{n^4 \over n^2+n!} < \epsilon
